I'm dealing with suicidal toughts when they injected me with Antipsychotics.. Everyday is a struggle since that moment.. At the moment I use Antipsychotics,Diazapam and Temezapam as Benzo's and ritalin for my ADHD.. 

Living like this makes me a zombie.. Only thing that keeps me alive each day is ritalin cuz it gives me a bit energy and a more clear mental mind.. But overcoming suicidal toughts everyday and each moment feels like a fight.

I Stopped driving with my car and working out because of the effects of the medicine.. Only advise I can give is to find something to life for each moments the toughts creep up.. Living in the moment and stop thinking about the future if you really feeling suicidal.

I also have the right people around me such as a coach, psychologist and psychiatrist who support my recovery. 

Really wish you the best.. But being in that state of mind all day.. the cure for me is to find blessings in the smallest things in the moment.
